subject: ENGLISH
text: Write a Composition, to fill about a page and a half of your book on one of the following subjects:

subject: ENGLISH
text: The Parables of the New Testament.

subject: ENGLISH
text: The story of the Lady of Shalott or of the Pied Piper of Hamelin.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Cavaliers and Roundheads.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Sunday in the country.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Lost in the jungle.

subject: ENGLISH
text: A day in the life of any one of the following: a deep-sea fisherman, a farm-servant, a tramway-conductor, a typist, a nurse.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Read the following passage carefully and then answer the questions on it:

subject: ENGLISH
text: Give in your own words a brief description of the Lombard Plain under these headings:

subject: ENGLISH
text: its boundaries;

subject: ENGLISH
text: i) the interior;

subject: ENGLISH
text: ii) its historical importance.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Explain the following phrases as used in the passage: the loud play of armies, an awful simplicity, seemingly impassable, their summit sharply defined against it.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Give the meaning of arena and indicate the aptness of its use in this passage.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Write down a word of the opposite meaning to each of the following—solemn, level, continuous, fertility, wealth.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Form an adjective from decide, a noun from fix, a verb from beauty. Substitute one word for the phrase like none other.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Put the following dialogue into reported speech.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Make a general analysis of the last sentence—"I am come here tonight."

subject: ENGLISH
text: Explain briefly the meaning of the following idioms: to let sleeping dogs lie, to take the bull by the horns, to put the cart before the horse, to be the black sheep of the family, to get the lion’s share, to let the cat out of the bag.

subject: ENGLISH
text: What is the meaning of the following abbreviations: O.H.M.S., V.C., M.P., A.D., MS., U.S.S.R., Esq., a.m., e.g.?
